# Git LFS — large binary/embedded design artifacts.
#
# The v5 web design prototype introduces boot audio and an intro video, and its
# self-contained HTML files base64-embed that media (~14 MB each). Tracking them
# via LFS keeps the git object database lean. Scoped to v5 on purpose: v1–v4 are
# small and stay as ordinary git blobs.
docs/design/web/v5/**/*.mp3 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
docs/design/web/v5/**/*.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
docs/design/web/v5/**/*.html filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Presentation exports (self-contained standalone HTML + rendered PDF, several MB
# each with embedded fonts/media). Same rationale as the v5 block: keep the git
# object database lean. Scoped to docs/presentations/ so future decks land here.
docs/presentations/**/*.html filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
docs/presentations/**/*.pdf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
